<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8151> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8151" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Although he was a Papius by birth and was adopted by his maternal grandfather T. Annius (Ascon. 53C), he appears not to have included the cognomen Papianus in his name (Shackleton Bailey, Studies 103).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5180> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5180" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic..Mil. 68. A candidate for the consulship of 52 (Ascon. 30 C)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5081> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5081" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In close co-operation with Sestius, he prepared street-gangs and met Clodius' violence with violence both while working for Cicero's recall from exile and after his return (Cic. Att. 4.3.3; Fam. 2.6.3; QF 1.4.3; P. Red. in Sen. 19-20, 30-31; P. Red. ad Quir. 15; Har. Resp. 6-7; Sest. 85-87, 90-92, 144; Vat. 40-41; Nil. 6, 38-39; Liv. Per. 104; Vell. 2.45.3; Ascon. 30 C; Plut. Cic. 33; App. BC 2.16; Dio 39.6-8; Schol. Bob. 122, 125, 169 Stangl). He attempted to prosecute Clodius for breach of the peace and impede his election to the aedileship (Cic. Att. 4.3.3- 4; Sest. 89; Mil. 40; Plut. Cic. 33; Dio 39.7-8)." .
